\pard\nowidctlpar\sb20\sa20\qc\fs56 the story:\par
\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\sb20\sa20\fs24\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\sb20\sa20\qc In the first part of Horns of Canzo, the Brotherhood of Fire informed \par
Garrett that they had kidnapped his friend Basso.  Basso's "ransom" \par
required Garrett to travel to Italy, then journey to an Italian mountain \par
named the Horns of Canzo, near the small village of Canzo.\par
\par
Garrett's first challenge was to reach room 4 of the infamous Third \par
Alp's Inn.  After a bit of trouble, he arrived and took the room.  For \par
three long days he lay studying the detailed information given him by \par
the Brotherhood. They made their demands quite clear:  Garrett was to \par
steal the priceless Dragon's Claw.\par
\par
The Dragon's Claw artifact is owned by Lord Kanfass; but Garrett learns \par
that Kanfass allows his protege, Mario Lombardi, to keep the artifact at \par
his beautiful villa.  Lombardi is mayor of Castlebrick, a small clump of \par
houses, hardly even a village, surrounded by a security wall.  \par
Lombardi's villa is just north of Castlebrick, and that is Garrett's \par
destination; for there the Claw is locked away in a huge, well-lit, \par
heavily guarded room that is watched night and day.\par
\par
In the third afternoon at the inn, Garrett grabs his weapons and \par
thieving equipment and sets out for Lombardi's villa.\par
